Installed Packages
Name       : mdadm
Arch       : i386
Version    : 2.6.9
Release    : 2.el5
Size       : 1.8 M
Repo       : installed
Summary    : mdadm controls Linux md devices (software RAID arrays)
URL        : http://www.kernel.org/pub/linux/utils/raid/mdadm/
License    : GPL
Description: mdadm is used to create, manage, and monitor Linux MD (software
           : RAID) devices.  As such, it provides similar functionality to the
           : raidtools package.  However, mdadm is a single program, and it can
           : perform almost all functions without a configuration file, though a
           : configuration file can be used to help with some common tasks.

